query.result:
58 His face seemed to me long and big 59 like the pine of Saint Peter in Rome, 60 and to its proportion were the other bones;
61 so that the bank, which was perizoma 62 from the middle downwards, showed us well so much 63 of above, that of reaching to the hair
64 three Frisians would have given themselves bad boast; 65 however that I saw there thirty great palms 66 from the place down where man hangs the mantle.

76 Then he said to me: “He himself accuses himself;  
77 this is Nembrotto for whose badly cooked  
78 even a language in the world is not used.”

79 Leave him be and we do not speak in vain;  
80 because thus each language is to him  
81 as his to others, which to no one is known.

94 Fïalte has name, and made the great trials  
95 when the giants made fear to the gods;  
96 the arms that he led, already never move.

124 Do not make us go to Tizio nor to Tifo:  
125 this one can give of what is desired here;  
126 but you bow and do not twist the griffin.

133 Virgil, when he felt to take,  
134 said to me: “Make yourself here, so that I may take you”;  
135 then he made it so that a bundle was him and me.
